runs.comm: on length outside off, Sagar pokes and is late on the shot so is beaten outside off
nice swing into the batsman towards off stump, he goes back and defends on the off side with his head down
beautiful shape again, coming into the batsman from back of length this time, pretty wide so it's left alone
too short, hardly any movement and this time Sagar rocks back to pull that in the air to the midwicket boundary from the middle of the bat
just back of length and into the batsman with some nice swing, he helps to midwicket for a quick single
too full this time, there's room too and he drills it straight to cover
absolutely full on the pads, he deflects it fine on the leg side for four more
much better looking, this time on the off side for four more! Fullish outside off, he leans towards it and drives it square past point all along the ground
touch back of length towards off this time, he defends off the back foot
pokes outside the off stump to touch the length delivery but is beaten
short and pretty wide, good bounce too, and he guides it to point
nice inswing this time, inside edge goes towards short leg and they sneak in a quick single
slightly slow and swinging in from length, he leans forward to help it to third man

oh, that's a run out after some hesitation! Airee swung his bat for the shorter and wider delivery to dispatch that between cover point and point. They were coming back for the third when he hesitated and even a dive could not save him
fullish with some inswing around off, pushed down the ground for one
wider outside off and Airee leans forward to help it to third man with a thick edge
nice inswing from slightly wide outside off, he lets it go
swinging in a bit from outside off, defends it to point

almost another run out, what an effort from Siaka at point! Airee cut the back of length ball off the back foot to point and went for the run, but was sent back and made it back because there was no direct hit
swing and a miss this time for the short delivery outside off
on length on off stump now, pushed down to mid off
touch shorter outside off, punched to cover
shorter and coming in, pulled to deep backward square leg for one
tad short of length outside off, punched to cover point
on length on the off stump with some inswing, pushed to midwicket
shorter and wider outside off, he defends it back
even wider outside off, he swings and misses this time
swings again, connects this time, but not from the middle and dispatches that over the covers for two
fuller, there's some room too and he connects better by lofting it down the ground to clear mid-off for four this time
top edge off the short ball and that goes over the keeper's head. He pulled but wasn't in a great position and managed to clear the keeper before Pala from first slip ran back
length delivery on middle stump, tucked towards midwicket for one
two of the three stumps have been uprooted at the non-striker's end! The full delivery was drilled down absolutely straight and it deflected towards mid-on who also conceded an overthrow
shorter outside off, he cuts it to point
full on middle and leg, clipped straight to midwicket
hits the off stump this time, slogs the fullish ball firmly down the ground and the ball deflects to mid-off this time
stifled appeal as he traps him in front of leg but it's going down leg
full on the pads, clipped nicely off the legs behind square on the leg side for a well-timed four

dropped at the boundary! The short ball was struck straight to deep backward square leg with a pull, Siaka got into position with his fingers pointing upwards for the catch at chedt-height and it went through his hands
short again, pulled again, this time wide of the fielder for a clean for this time
short and wide, he stays back to cut it uppishly, just wide of point for two in the gap
swing and a miss this time for the short delivery outside off, he didn't move much for that shot
short outside off and it's mistimed off a pull back to the bowler
he's lost his balance completely, he's lost his wicket too! Tossed up around middle, he shuffled across to sweep that with the turn and slipped while edging the ball to the stumps
pretty wide outside off, he looks to cut but withdraws in the end
turning towards the pads and he tucks it to deep square leg
not much turn outside off, he cuts and misses
slower through the air and closer to off, pushed along the ground to long off
some room outside off and it's punched off the back foot to deep cover
nice shape into the batsman outside off, defends it to cover
more towards off and he chips it down to mid-on after a bounce
outside off, he helps it to third man for one
opens up early to cover the stumps and scoop that length delivery from off stump over the keeper
fullish on the stumps, it's tucked down to long-on for one

it's the big wicket of Airee, he loses his off stump. He went for the slog as the ball swung in slightly towards the off stump, he missed and the ball struck the off stump. Airee s disappointed, naturally
turning in towards off, pushed down to long on for one
wider outside off and it's driven to cover point for one

bigger wicket, Paras also gone! It was a wide delivery outside off, on length, he leaned towards it and drove on the up to point. Pala had to dive forward and did it well to get his hands under the ball
length delivery outside off, driven to cover
keeps a bit low as it turns in towards middle stump, he blocks it back
drives the length delivery to cover this time
shuffles across to cover the stumps and tucks the ball to leg a bit dangerously
leans forward and pushes the ball into the covers
fuller and towards off, pushed back to the bowler
exposes his stumps completely by shuffling to off, and deflects the ball off the pads from well outside off to square leg. There was an appeal for lbw but it struck him outside off
beaten! Nice delivery as it looked to swing in but nearly held its line as Vesawkar poked and looked to withdraw his bat
fuller on the stumps, driven down to long on for one
turning into the batsman, tucked to midwicket
pushes the full delivery back to the bowler
charges down and slogs the ball to long on for one
takes a step down and pushes it down to long on
defends the ball back to the bowler off the front foot
comes down to take it on the full and pushes it back to the bowler again
almost a yorker on off stump, worked down to mid-on for one
short of length and just outside off, cut with a bottom edge towards third man for one
almost edged to the keeper! It was back of length outside off, he poked dangerously and missed!
run out chance, just missed! He tucked the full delivery on off stump down to mid-on and took if quickly. A direct hit at the bowler's end would have made it five down
touch shorter outside off with room, steers it to deep cover for one
coming in from back of length outside off, guides it late to third man for one
touch short of length towards off, pushed down to long on for one
charges down and slams the ball straight to hit his partner
goes down on a knee to slog-sweep that to long on for one
quicker outside off, he places that wide of short third man for a quick single
wider outside off, he waits for it and slams it down to long off for one
charges down to slog it just past the keeper for a single
too wide, mis-directed. Outside off stump, no way he can bat on that
attempts the yorker, in the block hole, tapped back to the bowler
a repeat of the first wide! Too wide and short outside off stump
Gone this time. He sticks to the shorter length outside off and he attempts to pull it, but it rushes on to him and he skies it for an easy chance to mid-off
full and wide outside off, would have been another wide but he flays at it and gets it down to third man where it is well fielded.
is he out ? he taps it to midwicket and sets off for a quick single, Dai is lurking there and picks it up and hits directly at the non-strikers end and he is well short. Nepal six down
darts it in on off and it is flicked easily to long-on
flatter on leg, easily tapped away to midwicket
darts it in again and shorter, tapped back to the bowler
flicked away towards deep midwicket and they are looking for two, they cant get it
slogged away straight to deep midwicket. Another wicket. Flatter and on off, Pulami comes down and looks to belt it over the boundary but picks out midwicket
flatter on off, patted back to the bowler
defended on the back foot back to the bowler
drifts down the leg side, hits his pad and trickles away towards fine leg
good line and length, hitting the top of off, guided behind point for an easy single
pitches on middle and straightening and is played away towards third man
good lines again. Kami can only find point this time
touch wider outside the off stump and is driven well to the sweeper cover

they don't get it. Suicidal run. Tapped away to cover where they set off for one and the throw is swift to the keeper, and he is nowhere close. Gone by a distance. It's the third run out of the innings
darts it in outside off and is guided away to short third man
flatter and outside off stump, played away to third man again
played to cover off the back foot
flatter again, tapped back to the bowler
he fires it in again, the batsman can find the gap at long-on this time
wide outside off, the batsman misses the cut
fuller on off and he hits it straight to midwicket
good yorker, batsman just gets down on it and they scamper one
easy catch! no trouble, and another wicket for PNG. Full toss and he bunts it off the front foot and skies it straight to midwicket. Nepal struggling here
full and quick on leg stump, and hits the batsman's pads and rolls away to fine leg
another low full toss. Drilled down to long-on
outside off and is played to point and the fielder picks it up and hits directly once again. He is just in, not much in it though
attempts the reverse sweep and misses comprehensively, big appeal but not given
slogged away to deep midwicket, can't get two
another wicket and Nepal are all out for just 93. Fires it in on middle and another slog which findes the outer half of the bat and carries to short third man for an easy take.
